refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;

 arrayfalseclass_implements
 objectstringobject_or_class
 boolautoload&true;



 This function returns an array with the names of the interfaces that the
 given object_or_class and its parents implement.

  &reftitle.examples;



    class_implements example


<?php

interface foo { }
class bar implements foo {}

print_r(class_implements(new bar));

// you may also specify the parameter as a string
print_r(class_implements('bar'));

spl_autoload_register();

// use autoloading to load the 'not_loaded' class
print_r(class_implements('not_loaded', true));

?>


    &example.outputs.similar;


Array
(
    [foo] => foo
)
Array
(
    [foo] => foo
)
Array
(
    [interface_of_not_loaded] => interface_of_not_loaded
)

&reftitle.notes;


  To check that an object implements an interface, &instanceof;
  or the is_a function should be used instead.
